kashaar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kashaar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/8/00 9:27:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> <br>
It appears that the level 44 spells for pure casters drop at this location, and the 39 spells for hybrid classes.  A typical drop seems to be either three, one, or no spells.<br>
<br>
Kashaar Daubendiek<br>
Lv 49 Erudite Wizard<br>
Last Resort<br>
Xegony<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/9/00 1:56:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Broodmother</span><hr size=1> Don't bother attacking the broodma; we did; Lure of Fire 100% resisted every cast by 2 L55 wizards.<br>
<br>
I heard, not confirmed, that a druid dotted it and it took an HOUR to kite kill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/9/00 2:02:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Enticement of Flame</span><hr size=1> I would urge those of us over L46 or so to forego getting Enticement of Flame; if you get the spell, consider giving to someone lower.  It does a mere 313 of damage and costs too much to cast, for anyone that has Draught. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uororo7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ororo7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/10/00 7:56:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> spells drop frequently at least...</span><hr size=1> Spells at the wurms drop frequently at least.  I kind of like this design by Verant...<br>
<br>
1) We know where the spells drop.<br>
2) There is enough room to fight one and not aggro the other<br>
3) Potential for spawn to be camped, but why? The exp is not great, and since the spells drop so frequently hopefully everyone can get their spells without paying through the nose.<br>
4) Enter invis, avoid the elder wurms who see through invis, and sit at the camp spot...ask for the spell after grouped wizzys get it...nice groups have been giving them away.<br>
<br>
These things hit hard, I would not advise soloing.  At least take a magi, and tank/healer even better.<br>
<br>
If you still have the choice, I'd advise keeping good giant faction, at least until you journey through the Giant City Kael, and pick up the Wakening Land token at the dragon portal.  Then at least you can always by-pass the giant city if need be.  Not that the portal area is safe by any means if dragons hate you.<br>
<br>
I'd like to hear if the Great Divide gg drops anywhere besides Icewell...not sure of fighting down there for a while.<br>
<br>
Anyone know yet....if you have Wakenings token, do you still need to carry Great Divide token to gate their?  Or does each successive token make previous token obsolete?<br>
<br>
-Ororo Windrider, 51 Channeler, MM <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udephtondisgustipated.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dephton Disgustipated</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/12/00 2:26:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells drop frequently at least...</span><hr size=1> If you have WL, you dont need the GD Tooth.  We got Translocate from Icewell Keep, and the druid GD Port there as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrindel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grindel</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/00 7:58:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.creighton.edu/~chrisj/elminster.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells drop frequently at least...</span><hr size=1> Regarding the Broodmore and her resists, she's like Vox or fire giants.  You have to be in melee range to hit her.  I ran through about 2 1/2 bubs of mana before I figured that one out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Was a great fight though! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sepp>Sepp</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/7/01 2:19:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ha!</span><hr size=1> &quot;I would urge those of us over L46 or so to forego getting Enticement of Flame; if you get the spell, consider giving to someone lower. It does a mere 313 of damage and costs too much to cast, for anyone that has Draught&quot;<br>
<br>
I went to Western Wastes with my guild, and Skyshrine.. im only level 52 but lure used to let me go anywhere regardless (Im not much for leveling, prefer raiding).  All these new ice monsters on Velious make Lure of Ice worthless... most of the dragons (save 1) in WW we pulled were Ice monsters, Lure of Ice useless.  Skyshrine &amp; Sirren Grotto had monsters that I could land Draught on but not Lure of Ice (immune to ice = IMMUNE to ice),and higher level mobs I couldnt land either.  Enticment of Flame may not do alot of damage, but atleast its some =P.  Getting that spell is my current top priority, gonna do it when I log on.. atleast i'll be more use than a photographer on high level mob raids =P (I got some badass screen shots though) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uasadd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Asadd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/7/01 5:20:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ha!</span><hr size=1> The reason they were getting Resisted is b/c this mob you have to be in Melee range to kill it.  Um group of 6 lvl 54+ Worked the bitch. <p>Asadd Forestlion<BR>
